I have been trying for baby since 2019. Undergone various treatments, laparoscopic surgeries but everything failed.  visited multiple doctors in Mumbai for second opinions but every-time I was more miserable as the only answer I got was UNEXPLAINED INFERTILITY. I had completely broken down and started having social stigma as always faced only one question when will you give good news? 

One of my distant relative recommended Dr Nutan Hegde to my mom. Frankly I had given up on mental peace, my mom said let’s please go here. I visited her in Dec 2022, conceived in Feb 23 and delivered a healthy baby in Oct 23.
She made me believe I am all good to conceive, she guided me positively on exercising, walking and most importantly diet. With mild  and few medicines she just made the magic happen. I feel fortunate enough to meet her and forever thankful to her for bringing in all the positivity without hurting my body with trucks of medicine. Unlike other doctors I never got a doctor vibe from her but more of a guide, philosopher and friend.

Would highly and always recommend her for any treatment as she makes things at ease for a patients and believes in getting positive results

review_reply.reply_text:
Thank you for your feedback.My most of the deliveries are normal. I motivate my patients from the very beginning for pelvic exercises so that they get into spontaneous labour.Every patient is explained about the process for normal and caesarean delivery and indications for caesarean delivery. I decided for caesarean after doing NST which ddnt look good and was explained to u and ur relatives. At that time I couldn’t even wait for a normal delivery as u were in early labour and would take 6-8 hours for full dilation and delivery. But it would jeopardise the baby’s condition. I had also explained to u about baby having passed motion inside which I saw during the Caesarean. It’s called foetal distress and this dirty fluid may get into baby’s lungs to cause infection.
I don’t push any patient for caesarean until there is a strong reason.
With respect to the hospital and facilities u were given a list of hospitals and choose accordingly.
